Hi.  We where there on Saturday the 20th during the market. There were four of us and my very well behaved dog. We sat in the first booth on the right trying to have lunch and a couple of drinks.  Our server got the drinks wrong and took 15 minutes to bring new. We ended up going to the bar to get some and paid cash. Again, the same thing happened with the next drinks.  We ordered food and an hour later she said our order never went through. She said we would not be charged for anything. After another half hour she brought us Togo cups and apologized because the food was never started.  We left the restaurant with her standing right next to us explaining that this service is not tolerated and she would take care of it.   We came back later that evening to try again after hearing how good the food was and were told we were not welcome to leave because we never paid for our drinks and to get the dog out because he wasn’t a service dog.  Very disappointed!!!!!  We would have never walked out on a bill it she told us we were all set.

The past several weekends a small group of us have ordered meals from here and had good results. Tonight, an hour after being placed, our delivery order was cancelled with no explanation. When we called (planning to reorder thinking it was an issue with the delivery service) we were told that our $100+ order had been cancelled because it had been requested to replace fries with onion rings. Mind you, this is something we’ve done in the past with no issue so it was a bit shocking that this has occurred. After a bit of a discussion and feedback that they should have the delivery service update options, an employee told my friend that she was rude. At this point, she turned on the speaker phone so that we could all hear both sides of the conversations. After challenging what had happened as well as the fact that we’ve had no issues before, the person told her she was “Incompetent” and ended the call. Literally all of our jaws dropped by this shocking lack of professionalism and courtesy. We’ve been very intentional during the crisis to support local businesses, but it looks likely that this will be the last time that any of us support this business. Horrible customer service. Allegedly the person we were talking with was the manager and his name is John Davis. If this is the case, I’d highly recommend a new manager who represents your business properly.
